I wanted something small and after comparing various products with other companies, I decided to purchase this one. Even compared to Chinese products with 3000 to 3500 lumens, they are brighter and have better image quality. I was surprised at how vivid the images were considering the size of the device. I was impressed and shocked to see how much the same projector from a major manufacturer can change. However, the brightness changes depending on whether it's connected to a power source or when it's on battery power, which is a bit disappointing. It's more expensive than a Chinese product with the same HD resolution, but the catalog specs aren't everything, so I think it's worth buying this one even if you spend a little more on it. Even when comparing major products in the same price range, the resolution of other companies is one step lower than HD, so I think this is a product that does its best in terms of price. Partly because I bought it after getting used to Chinese loud fans, I felt it was quiet on a different level. The fan noise changes depending on whether Eco mode is on or off, low, or high, but even with the noisiest eco mode off, the sound was loud enough that it didn't bother me, who is sensitive to sounds, and I was able to concentrate on the image. This projector has a maximum power of 55W. A typical Chinese projector with the same specs costs several times as much, so I think it's by far the best in terms of power consumption. Depending on the settings, there is very little heat generation, and I am convinced that this difference is the strength of a major product. Due to its energy-saving structure, even when using the main battery, continuous use was possible for about 90 minutes with Eco mode off, about 110-120 minutes with Eco mode low, and about 170-180 minutes with Eco mode high. Naturally, it will be shorter than the above depending on various settings and whether there is a wireless connection, so please use it as a reference only. One feature that Chinese projectors do not have is an automatic keystone correction function, which automatically corrects the image to a beautiful rectangle even if the image is projected at an angle. This feature was a big hit for me. There was no problem even if I attached a tripod to the projector and projected at an angle. I'd give it a 5-star rating if I were just looking at the main body, but the fact that a lens cover isn't included and the included special pouch is just a bonus, so I'll give it a -1 star rating because of those two points. There is also a full HD compatible version of the higher-end model, but while the overall specs have improved, the price has also increased and the fan noise has become a bit noisy, so I think this model is still a good buy.

When I checked the write capacity using a tool called h2testw, I found that I could only write 32GB out of 128GB. After checking Windows error and bad sectors, the display on the OS became 32GB. Purchased to protect the LCD of AQUOS sense SH-01K. There are no problems with this product itself, and the anti-reflection properties seem to be reasonably good. The surface of the LCD panel on a normal terminal is flat glass or plastic up to the four corners, but the AQUOS sense SH-01K's panel has an R shape on the four sides and is not flat. Therefore, the protective film is applied only to the flat part inside the R shape, so there is no separation, and there is no protective film around the entire periphery, making it difficult to apply it in a balanced manner. This is a problem with AQUOS sense SH-01K and this product is not responsible at all.

I had never spent money on a hair dryer before, so I used a cheap hair dryer that I received. A friend told me that there are many cheap but good hair dryers these days, so I decided on this one, which is affordable even for beginner hair dryers. To be honest, I was surprised the first time I dried it! I don't know if it's the effect of the ions, but my hair felt smooth just by drying it! I wish I had bought it sooner. It's not compact, but it's the type you often see at barber shops, and it's powerful and suitable for drying hair in a short amount of time. The price is also low compared to the performance, and the cost performance is good. It's good because it produces a lot of wind power with no noise. I feel like I'm feeling smoother than usual! The smell of the product? I'm a little concerned. Will it disappear eventually? That's what I thought, but it didn't go away after about a month. However, other than that, the usability is very good. Sometimes cheap hair dryers have very low airflow or the air is lukewarm, but this dryer has plenty of airflow and is hot. I bought this hair dryer about 6 years ago (back then, the logo was National) and it was completely unbreakable and was usable, but just the other day when I used it to crack open a headlight, it broke and the same thing happened again. I bought things again. It won't break if you use it normally, and I think it's quite durable.I have two block long hair, and it's a good product as it doesn't compare to the 1,000 yen hair dryer I used before. It feels shiny after being dried. LEDs are bright. Although it is light and compact, it has plenty of airflow and dries quickly. The hot air isn't too hot, so there's less damage to your hair. My hair regained its luster on the second day of use. I was quite worried about the price, but so far I'm very satisfied because the usability is very good. I hope I can use it for a long time.

This is a far cry from what you would normally imagine from the term "design recipe collection." Most of the code is pretty basic. Rather, is this basic code a design recipe? This is an amazing book in my opinion. Normally, I would like to give a low review rating because of the discrepancy between the title and the content, but this book is surprisingly useful. This is because each basic code is explained in detail one by one. In particular, there are several patterns for the same design depending on the situation, and the currently mainstream methods are explained along with their reasons. If you read this carefully, even if you work in web design or coding, you will probably discover many new things you didn't know before. [Good points] - Deep explanation of the basic codes - Codes for different situations are available - You can learn the basics of the basics [Bad points] - The content of the book that you associate with the title is quite different from the actual content There is a discrepancy. This content is not about how to do that design or how to express an attractive design. [Summary] - There are no books that thoroughly explain simple basic codes in such a comprehensive manner. The value is high. - It is suitable for checking how to use basic code, not for reverse lookup of the design you want. - Suitable for those learning chords for the first time to practice one by one.

It seems that running uses an accelerometer to measure speed and distance, while cycling uses smartphone location information to measure speed and distance. The problem is the connection with the smartphone, and if the connection with Bluetooth becomes unstable, location information will be lost and speed and distance will not be collected. I've tried putting it in my back pocket, in my backpack, and in my chest pocket, but no matter where I put my smartphone, it loses location information to varying degrees, almost 100%. Once it's lost, it doesn't seem to recover automatically, so you need to restart the device and get the location information again (Answer from customer center) If it's around 5,000 yen, I can laugh and forgive it, but I think this specification is a little out of the question for anything over 10,000 yen. Masu. I think that if you lose your location information, all you have to do is send a location information request to your smartphone again, but not being able to do that is a bug in the specifications, and not doing so is negligence on the part of the manufacturer.

I often see reports of not being able to adjust colors, but this is also not possible. *Updated on 2/26: It seems that this has now been fixed in the driver. They respond quickly and are very nice. I saw it somewhere, but if a liquid tablet that can be used with Wacom pens comes out, I would like to purchase it. I wish they would put more effort into pen development.
